            ['What does your father do?', 'My father is a teacher. He works at a school. He teaches math to children.', 'Say the job + where.', ['teacher', 'school', 'teach', 'math']],
            ['What job do you want?', 'I want to be a doctor. I want to help sick people. Doctors are important.', 'Use "I want to be a" + why.', ['doctor', 'sick', 'help', 'important']],
            ['Do you work?', 'No, I am a student. I study at school. My sister works in a shop.', 'Say your job or that you study.', ['work', 'student', 'study', 'shop']],
            ['Where do you work or study?', 'I study at a school near my house. I go there by bus. It is a big school.', 'Say where + one detail.', ['study', 'school', 'bus', 'big']],
            ['What is an easy job?', 'I think a shop worker has an easy job. They sell things and talk to people. But every job is tiring.', 'Name a job + why it is easy.', ['shop worker', 'sell', 'tiring', 'easy']],
            ['Do you like your job or school?', 'Yes, I like school. I learn new things and meet friends. But homework is hard.', 'Say yes/no + one reason.', ['learn', 'friends', 'homework', 'hard']],
        ],
        'A2' => [
            ['Describe your job or your studies.', 'I work as a shop assistant in a clothes shop. I help customers and arrange the clothes. I work from 9 to 5, Monday to Friday.', 'Mention role + tasks + hours.', ['shop assistant', 'customer', 'arrange', 'from 9 to 5']],
            ['What do you want to be in the future?', 'In the future I want to be an engineer. I like building things and solving problems. I will study engineering at university.', 'Use future tense + reasons.', ['engineer', 'build', 'solve problems', 'university']],
            ['Do you prefer working alone or in a team?', 'I prefer working in a team because we can share ideas. It is more fun and we learn from each other. But sometimes I like to work alone to focus.', 'State preference + reason.', ['team', 'share ideas', 'focus', 'alone']],
            ['What is a difficult part of your job or studies?', 'The most difficult part is the long hours. I feel tired in the evening. Exams are also very stressful for me.', 'Mention 1–2 difficulties.', ['long hours', 'tired', 'exam', 'stressful']],
            ['Talk about a person who inspired your career choice.', 'My uncle is a chef, and he inspired me to love cooking. He works hard and enjoys his job. Watching him made me want to be a chef too.', 'Describe the person + their influence.', ['chef', 'inspire', 'enjoy', 'career']],
            ['Is money or enjoyment more important in a job?', 'I think enjoyment is more important. If you enjoy your job, you do it well and money comes later. But money is also needed to live.', 'Weigh both factors.', ['enjoyment', 'money', 'do well', 'live']],
        ],
        'B1' => [
            ['How did you choose your current career path?', 'I chose my path partly by chance. I enjoyed writing at school, so I studied communications. An internship at a magazine showed me I loved it, and I\'ve worked in content ever since. It was less a plan than a series of good decisions.', 'Use a mix of tenses to tell the story.', ['by chance', 'internship', 'content', 'decision']],
            ['What are the most important qualities for success at work?', 'I\'d say reliability, adaptability and good communication. Skills can be taught, but someone who can\'t work with others or adapt to change will struggle. Curiosity matters too — the best colleagues keep learning.', 'List qualities and explain why each matters.', ['reliability', 'adaptability', 'curiosity', 'colleague']],
            ['Do you think working from home is a good idea?', 'For many jobs, yes. It saves commuting time and lets people focus, which boosts productivity. But it can also feel isolating, and teamwork sometimes suffers. A hybrid model seems to be the best balance.', 'Give a balanced view with a conclusion.', ['commuting', 'productivity', 'isolating', 'hybrid']],
            ['Describe a challenging situation at work and how you handled it.', 'Once a project deadline was moved up by a week with no warning. I stayed calm, prioritised the most important tasks, and asked my team for help. We delivered on time, and I learned the value of clear communication under pressure.', 'Use narrative + reflection.', ['deadline', 'prioritise', 'pressure', 'deliver']],
            ['How important is work-life balance to you?', 'It\'s essential. Early in my career I overworked and burned out, which taught me that rest isn\'t lazy — it\'s necessary. I now set clear boundaries, and I\'m both happier and more productive.', 'Share a personal lesson.', ['work-life balance', 'burn out', 'boundary', 'productive']],
            ['Would you rather have a high salary or a meaningful job?', 'I\'d lean towards a meaningful job, because waking up motivated every day is worth more than money. That said, a job should pay enough to live comfortably. The ideal is a role that is both meaningful and fairly paid.', 'Express a preference with a condition.', ['meaningful', 'motivated', 'comfortably', 'fairly']],
        ],
        'B2' => [
            ['"A career is something you build; a job is something you do." Discuss.', 'I think this captures an important distinction. A job pays the bills, while a career is a long-term trajectory that grows with you. The danger is treating a mere job as disposable, or sacrificing your life for a career that doesn\'t fulfil you. Ideally, they overlap.', 'Engage with the quotation analytically.', ['distinction', 'trajectory', 'disposable', 'fulfil']],
            ['How might AI and automation reshape the job market in the next decade?', 'I expect routine, repetitive work to be most affected, while creative and people-focused roles will be safer — at least initially. The bigger challenge is the transition: many workers will need retraining, and inequality could widen if we don\'t manage it carefully. New kinds of jobs will appear, but the gap may be painful.', 'Use prediction language + discuss consequences.', ['automation', 'repetitive', 'retraining', 'inequality']],
            ['Is the concept of a "job for life" outdated, and is that a good thing?', 'It\'s largely outdated, and I think that\'s mostly positive. People change and grow, and being locked into one path can be stifling. The trade-off is less security, so society needs stronger safety nets. Mobility is liberating, but only if the risks are shared.', 'Weigh freedom against security.', ['outdated', 'stifling', 'safety net', 'mobility']],
            ['Discuss the role of failure in building a successful career.', 'Failure is one of the most underrated teachers. Each setback shows you what doesn\'t work and builds resilience, which is essential for long-term success. People who never fail have usually never taken a real risk. The key is failing intelligently — learning without repeating the same mistake.', 'Use abstract, reflective vocabulary.', ['underrated', 'setback', 'resilience', 'intelligently']],
            ['How do cultural attitudes towards work differ around the world?', 'Attitudes vary enormously. Some cultures glorify long hours as a sign of dedication, while others protect leisure time fiercely. In parts of Europe, long holidays are normal, whereas elsewhere overtime is expected. Neither is objectively right, but the differences reveal what each society values most.', 'Use comparative structures and examples.', ['glorify', 'dedication', 'leisure', 'overtime']],
            ['Should people pursue passion or stability when choosing a career?', 'It depends on circumstance. If you have few responsibilities, pursuing passion makes sense — the risk is low and the reward is high. With a family to support, stability may take priority. The healthiest approach is to find where passion and stability overlap, even if it takes time.', 'Frame the answer conditionally.', ['pursue', 'stability', 'responsibility', 'overlap']],
        ],
    ],

    // ============================================================
    // 6. HOBBIES & INTERESTS
    // ============================================================
    'hobbies-interests' => [
        'A1' => [
            ['What do you do in your free time?', 'In my free time I play football. I also like reading books. Sometimes I watch TV.', 'List 2–3 free-time activities.', ['free time', 'football', 'read', 'watch TV']],
            ['Do you like music?', 'Yes, I like music very much. I listen to pop songs. My favourite singer is Taylor Swift.', 'Say yes/no + what you listen to.', ['music', 'pop song', 'singer', 'listen']],
            ['Can you play a sport?', 'Yes, I can play badminton. I play with my brother. I am not very good, but I enjoy it.', 'Say a sport + who you play with.', ['badminton', 'play', 'enjoy', 'good']],
            ['What is your hobby?', 'My hobby is drawing. I draw animals and flowers. I draw in my notebook every day.', 'Name your hobby + what you make.', ['hobby', 'draw', 'animal', 'flower']],
            ['Do you like reading?', 'Yes, I like reading. I read story books. My favourite book is about a wizard.', 'Say yes/no + what you read.', ['reading', 'story book', 'wizard', 'favourite']],
            ['What games do you play?', 'I play chess and video games. I play chess with my father. I play video games on my phone.', 'Name 2 games + where/with whom.', ['chess', 'video game', 'phone', 'play']],
        ],
        'A2' => [
            ['Describe a hobby you enjoy.', 'I really enjoy photography. I take photos of nature and streets. I use my phone, but I want to buy a real camera. It helps me see beauty in small things.', 'Describe the hobby + why you like it.', ['photography', 'nature', 'camera', 'beauty']],
            ['How often do you do your hobby?', 'I do my hobby every weekend. Sometimes I also draw in the evening after work. It depends on how busy I am.', 'Mention frequency + conditions.', ['every weekend', 'busy', 'evening', 'depend']],
            ['Do you prefer indoor or outdoor activities?', 'I prefer outdoor activities because I like fresh air and sunshine. Hiking is my favourite. But when it rains, I stay inside and read.', 'State preference + reason.', ['outdoor', 'fresh air', 'hiking', 'rain']],
            ['Talk about a hobby you would like to try.', 'I would like to try pottery. It looks relaxing to make things with clay. I saw a video online and I think it would be fun.', 'Use "I would like to try" + reason.', ['pottery', 'clay', 'relaxing', 'fun']],
            ['Have your hobbies changed over time?', 'Yes, when I was young I collected stamps. Now I prefer digital hobbies like editing videos. My interests change as I grow.', 'Use past + present contrast.', ['collect stamps', 'digital', 'edit videos', 'interest']],
            ['What hobby is popular in your country?', 'A popular hobby in my country is football. Many children play it in the street. Badminton is also very popular.', 'Name a hobby + who does it.', ['popular', 'football', 'street', 'badminton']],
        ],
        'B1' => [
            ['How did you get into your favourite hobby?', 'I got into cooking during the pandemic. With restaurants closed, I started watching tutorials and experimenting. What began as boredom turned into a real passion, and now I cook almost every day.', 'Tell the story of how it started.', ['get into', 'tutorial', 'experiment', 'passion']],
            ['Do you think hobbies are important for mental health?', 'Absolutely. Hobbies give us a break from stress and a sense of achievement that isn\'t tied to work. When I\'m painting, I lose track of time, which is a kind of meditation. They recharge us in ways rest alone can\'t.', 'Explain the mental-health benefit.', ['achievement', 'lose track of time', 'meditation', 'recharge']],
            ['Describe a hobby that taught you an unexpected skill.', 'Gardening taught me patience. Plants grow on their own schedule, and you can\'t rush them. I used to be quite impatient, but caring for plants has made me calmer and more accepting of slow progress.', 'Connect hobby to a personal change.', ['patience', 'schedule', 'rush', 'calm']],
            ['Is it better to have one serious hobby or many casual ones?', 'I think both have value. A serious hobby builds deep expertise and identity, while casual ones keep life varied and social. Personally, I keep one main hobby and a few lighter ones for balance.', 'Compare and find a personal balance.', ['expertise', 'identity', 'varied', 'balance']],
            ['Have you ever turned a hobby into something more serious?', 'Yes — I loved taking photos as a hobby, and friends started asking me to shoot their events. Eventually I began charging, and it became a small side business. It taught me that passion can become a career if you\'re willing to work at it.', 'Use narrative + reflection.', ['event', 'charge', 'side business', 'passion']],
            ['How do hobbies help people connect with others?', 'Hobbies create instant common ground. When you meet someone who shares your interest, conversation flows easily. Clubs and online communities turn solitary hobbies into social ones, which is especially valuable in a lonely modern world.', 'Explain the social function.', ['common ground', 'flow', 'community', 'solitary']],
        ],
        'B2' => [
            ['"Hobbies are the antidote to modern burnout." Discuss.', 'I largely agree. In a culture that turns every activity into productivity, hobbies reclaim time for its own sake. They offer flow without pressure, which is precisely what burned-out people lack. Whether they\'re a complete antidote is debatable, but they\'re certainly part of the cure.', 'Engage critically with the claim.', ['antidote', 'reclaim', 'flow', 'debatable']],
            ['How has the internet changed the way people pursue hobbies?', 'The internet has democratised expertise — anyone can learn almost anything for free, which has exploded the range of hobbies people try. It has also connected enthusiasts globally. The downside is that hobbies can become performative, done for an audience rather than for joy.', 'Weigh democratisation against performativity.', ['democratise', 'expertise', 'enthusiast', 'performative']],
            ['Can a hobby become harmful, and where is the line?', 'Yes. Any passion can tip into obsession — when it crowds out relationships, sleep or responsibilities, it\'s no longer healthy. The line is crossed when the hobby stops being a choice and starts being a compulsion. Awareness and balance are what keep hobbies life-giving.', 'Use conditional reasoning.', ['obsession', 'crowd out', 'compulsion', 'life-giving']],
            ['Discuss the difference between consumption-based and creation-based hobbies.', 'Consumption-based hobbies, like binge-watching, are passive and easy but rarely fulfilling long-term. Creation-based ones, like writing or woodworking, demand effort but build skill and identity. I think we need both, but a life built only on consumption tends to feel empty.', 'Contrast two categories thoughtfully.', ['consumption', 'binge-watching', 'woodworking', 'fulfilling']],
            ['Should schools give more importance to hobbies and the arts?', 'I believe so. Schools increasingly prioritise exam subjects, which narrows children\'s sense of what matters. Hobbies and the arts develop creativity, resilience and self-knowledge that academic subjects alone can\'t. A balanced education nurtures the whole person, not just the test-taker.', 'Argue with reasons and broader vision.', ['prioritise', 'resilience', 'self-knowledge', 'nurture']],
            ['How might hobbies evolve as technology advances?', 'I expect more hobbies to blend physical and digital — think augmented-reality art or AI-assisted music production. Virtual reality could make expensive hobbies like flying or sculpting accessible to many. Whether these feel as satisfying as traditional ones is the open question, but the range of possibilities is extraordinary.', 'Speculate with specific examples.', ['augmented reality', 'accessible', 'satisfying', 'extraordinary']],
        ],
    ],

    // ============================================================
    // 7. EDUCATION
    // ============================================================
    'education' => [
        'A1' => [
            ['Do you like school?', 'Yes, I like school. I learn new things. My teachers are kind. I play with my friends.', 'Say yes/no + 2 reasons.', ['school', 'learn', 'teacher', 'friend']],
            ['What is your favourite subject?', 'My favourite subject is math. I like numbers. It is fun for me. English is also nice.', 'Name the subject + why.', ['subject', 'math', 'number', 'fun']],
            ['What time does school start?', 'School starts at 7 in the morning. It finishes at 2 in the afternoon. I go home by bus.', 'Say the start + end time.', ['start', 'finish', 'afternoon', 'bus']],
            ['Do you have homework?', 'Yes, I have homework every day. I do it after dinner. Math homework is the hardest.', 'Say yes/no + when you do it.', ['homework', 'every day', 'dinner', 'hard']],
            ['Who is your favourite teacher?', 'My favourite teacher is Mr. Budi. He teaches science. He is funny and kind.', 'Name the teacher + subject + why.', ['teacher', 'science', 'funny', 'kind']],
            ['What do you want to study?', 'I want to study art. I like drawing. I want to be an artist one day.', 'Use "I want to study" + why.', ['study', 'art', 'draw', 'artist']],
        ],
        'A2' => [
            ['Describe your school.', 'My school is big and clean. There are many classrooms and a large field. The teachers are friendly, and I have good friends there.', 'Mention size + facilities + people.', ['big', 'classroom', 'field', 'friendly']],
            ['What subject is difficult for you?', 'History is difficult for me because there are many dates to remember. I try to study hard, but I forget sometimes.', 'Name the subject + why + what you do.', ['history', 'date', 'remember', 'forget']],
            ['Do you prefer studying alone or with friends?', 'I prefer studying with friends because we can help each other. But for difficult topics, I study alone to focus.', 'State preference + reason.', ['alone', 'with friends', 'help', 'focus']],
            ['How do you prepare for exams?', 'I start studying two weeks before. I make notes and review them every day. I also practise with old exam papers.', 'Mention methods + timing.', ['prepare', 'notes', 'review', 'practise']],
            ['Talk about a useful thing you learned at school.', 'I learned how to use a computer at school. Now I can type and search the internet. It is very useful for my studies.', 'Describe what you learned + why useful.', ['computer', 'type', 'search', 'useful']],
            ['Do you want to go to university?', 'Yes, I want to go to university. I want to study engineering. It will help me get a good job.', 'Say yes/no + what you want to study.', ['university', 'engineering', 'study', 'job']],
        ],
        'B1' => [
            ['How has your attitude towards learning changed over the years?', 'When I was younger I saw learning as something I had to do for grades. Now I see it as a lifelong process that enriches my life. I read and take courses out of curiosity, not obligation, which makes learning far more enjoyable.', 'Contrast past and present attitudes.', ['grades', 'lifelong', 'enrich', 'curiosity']],
            ['Do you think exams are a fair way to measure ability?', 'Partly. Exams test memory and pressure-handling, which matter, but they miss creativity, teamwork and practical skill. Some brilliant people perform poorly under exam conditions. I think they\'re a useful but incomplete measure.', 'Acknowledge strengths and limits.', ['measure', 'pressure-handling', 'brilliant', 'incomplete']],
            ['Describe a teacher who influenced you.', 'My literature teacher, Ms. Sari, changed how I think. She didn\'t just teach facts — she pushed us to question and to think for ourselves. Because of her, I fell in love with reading and learned to express my ideas clearly.', 'Use specific detail + impact.', ['literature', 'question', 'think for oneself', 'express']],
            ['Is online learning as effective as classroom learning?', 'It depends on the subject and the learner. Online learning is flexible and self-paced, which suits motivated people. But classrooms offer structure, social interaction and immediate feedback. A blended approach often works best.', 'Compare with conditions and nuance.', ['flexible', 'self-paced', 'motivated', 'blended']],
            ['What would you change about the education system in your country?', 'I would reduce the emphasis on rote memorisation and high-stakes exams. I\'d introduce more project-based learning and critical thinking. Students should learn how to think, not just what to remember.', 'Use "would" + reasons.', ['rote memorisation', 'high-stakes', 'project-based', 'critical thinking']],
            ['How important is education for success in life?', 'Education opens doors and builds a foundation, but it isn\'t the only path to success. Character, resilience and relationships matter just as much. Education gives you tools; what you build with them is up to you.', 'Acknowledge importance + add nuance.', ['foundation', 'character', 'resilience', 'up to you']],
        ],
        'B2' => [
            ['"Education is what remains after one has forgotten what one learned in school." Discuss.', 'This suggests that real education is about habits of mind — curiosity, discipline, critical thinking — not facts that fade. I largely agree. The specific formulas I\'ve forgotten matter less than the ability to learn, question and adapt, which school ideally cultivates.', 'Interpret the quotation and take a stance.', ['habit of mind', 'fade', 'cultivate', 'adapt']],
            ['How might education need to change for an AI-driven future?', 'If AI can answer any factual question, education must shift from memorising to evaluating, creating and collaborating. Students will need strong judgement to assess AI outputs and ethical reasoning to use them responsibly. Adaptability, not knowledge stockpiling, will define the educated person.', 'Use forward-looking, analytical language.', ['evaluate', 'collaborate', 'judgement', 'stockpiling']],
            ['Is formal education becoming less relevant?', 'It\'s becoming less of a monopoly. With information freely available, self-taught people can rival degree-holders in many fields. However, formal education still offers structure, credentials and networks that are hard to replicate. It\'s not irrelevant, but it must justify itself more than before.', 'Frame as a shifting role, not a binary.', ['monopoly', 'self-taught', 'credential', 'justify']],
            ['Discuss the value of arts and humanities in a STEM-focused world.', 'STEM drives innovation, but the humanities give it direction and meaning. Without ethics, history and culture, technical progress can be aimless or even harmful. The best solutions come from people who understand both how things work and why they matter.', 'Argue for balance with reasoning.', ['STEM', 'humanities', 'ethics', 'aimless']],
            ['Should education be free for everyone?', 'In principle, yes — education is a public good that benefits society as a whole. In practice, free systems can struggle with quality and funding. The real question is how to make quality education accessible without overburdening taxpayers, which likely means targeted support rather than blanket free tuition.', 'Distinguish principle from practice.', ['public good', 'funding', 'taxpayer', 'targeted']],
            ['How does education reproduce or reduce social inequality?', 'Education can do both. On one hand, it\'s the main ladder out of poverty. On the other, unequal funding and access often reproduce existing privilege. Whether education reduces or reinforces inequality depends less on schools themselves than on the society that shapes them.', 'Hold a tension without false resolution.', ['reproduce', 'privilege', 'funding', 'ladder']],
        ],
    ],

    // ============================================================
    // 8. TECHNOLOGY
    // ============================================================
    'technology' => [
        'A1' => [
            ['Do you have a phone?', 'Yes, I have a phone. I use it to call my mom and play games. I love my phone.', 'Say yes/no + 2 uses.', ['phone', 'call', 'game', 'use']],
            ['Do you like computers?', 'Yes, I like computers. I play games and watch videos. My father works on a computer.', 'Say yes/no + what you do.', ['computer', 'game', 'video', 'work']],
            ['What do you do on the internet?', 'On the internet I watch videos and play games. I also chat with my friends. It is fun.', 'List 2–3 online activities.', ['internet', 'video', 'chat', 'fun']],
            ['Can you use a tablet?', 'Yes, I can use a tablet. I draw on it and read stories. My little sister uses it too.', 'Say yes/no + what you do.', ['tablet', 'draw', 'read', 'story']],
            ['Do you play video games?', 'Yes, I play video games. My favourite game is Minecraft. I play it on weekends.', 'Say yes/no + favourite game.', ['video game', 'Minecraft', 'weekend', 'favourite']],
            ['What is your favourite gadget?', 'My favourite gadget is my phone. I take photos and listen to music on it.', 'Name the gadget + 2 uses.', ['gadget', 'photo', 'music', 'phone']],
        ],
        'A2' => [
            ['How often do you use the internet?', 'I use the internet every day. I check it in the morning and at night. I use it for school and for fun.', 'Mention frequency + purposes.', ['internet', 'every day', 'school', 'fun']],
            ['Do you think technology is good or bad?', 'I think technology is mostly good. It helps us learn and connect. But too much phone time is bad for our eyes and sleep.', 'Weigh both sides.', ['technology', 'connect', 'eyes', 'sleep']],
            ['Describe an app you use a lot.', 'I use a messaging app every day. I send messages and photos to my friends. It is free and very fast.', 'Name the app + what you do.', ['app', 'message', 'photo', 'free']],
            ['What would you do without your phone for a day?', 'Without my phone, I would feel bored at first. Then I would read a book or go outside. It might actually be relaxing.', 'Use "I would" + imagine the day.', ['without', 'bored', 'relax', 'outside']],
            ['Do you prefer reading on paper or on a screen?', 'I prefer paper books because they are easier on my eyes. But screens are convenient because I can carry many books on one device.', 'State preference + reasons.', ['paper', 'screen', 'eyes', 'convenient']],
            ['Talk about a new technology you like.', 'I like wireless earphones. I can listen to music anywhere without wires. The sound is clear and they are small.', 'Describe the tech + why you like it.', ['wireless', 'earphone', 'wire', 'sound']],
        ],
        'B1' => [
            ['How has technology changed the way we communicate?', 'Technology has made communication instant and global. I can video-call family on the other side of the world for free. But it\'s also made conversations shallower — we text instead of talk, which can feel less personal.', 'Weigh benefits and drawbacks.', ['instant', 'global', 'video-call', 'shallow']],
            ['Do you think social media does more harm than good?', 'It\'s a real trade-off. Social media connects people and gives everyone a voice, which is powerful. But it also fuels anxiety, comparison and misinformation. I think it\'s neutral — the harm comes from how we use it.', 'Present a balanced trade-off.', ['trade-off', 'voice', 'anxiety', 'misinformation']],
            ['Describe a piece of technology you couldn\'t live without.', 'I honestly couldn\'t live without my laptop. I work, study, and stay in touch with people through it. Losing it for a week once showed me how dependent I\'ve become — which made me a little uncomfortable.', 'Use a personal anecdote + reflection.', ['dependent', 'laptop', 'lose', 'uncomfortable']],
            ['Should children be allowed to use smartphones?', 'With limits, yes. Smartphones can be educational, but young children lack the self-control to manage them. I think parents should delay giving smartphones and set clear rules about screen time and content.', 'Express a conditional opinion.', ['educational', 'self-control', 'delay', 'screen time']],
            ['How do you manage your screen time?', 'I set app limits and keep my phone out of the bedroom at night. I also take one screen-free day a week. These small rules keep technology as a tool rather than a habit.', 'Share practical strategies.', ['app limit', 'screen-free', 'tool', 'habit']],
            ['What technology do you think will be big in the next few years?', 'I think AI assistants will become part of daily life, like smartphones did. Augmented reality could also change how we shop and learn. The challenge will be making sure these tools serve us, not the other way around.', 'Make a prediction + a concern.', ['AI assistant', 'augmented reality', 'serve', 'challenge']],
        ],
        'B2' => [
            ['"Technology is a useful servant but a dangerous master." Discuss.', 'This captures my view well. Technology amplifies human intention — for connection, for knowledge, for harm. The danger is when we stop choosing how to use it and let its design choices govern our behaviour. The question is whether we can keep it as a servant as it grows more powerful.', 'Interpret the metaphor and extend it.', ['amplify', 'intention', 'govern', 'servant']],
            ['How should society balance privacy and convenience?', 'It\'s one of the defining tensions of our era. Convenience often asks us to trade personal data, and most of us accept without reading the terms. I think we need stronger regulation and better defaults, because individuals can\'t realistically negotiate with tech giants alone.', 'Frame as a structural problem, not individual.', ['tension', 'default', 'regulation', 'negotiate']],
            ['Discuss the ethical implications of AI making decisions about people.', 'When AI approves loans, screens CVs or predicts recidivism, the stakes are human lives. The danger is that opaque systems launder bias as "objective". I think transparency, auditing and human oversight are essential — efficiency can\'t come at the cost of fairness.', 'Use domain vocabulary and reasoning.', ['recidivism', 'opaque', 'launder bias', 'auditing']],
            ['Is the digital divide widening or narrowing?', 'Both, in different ways. Access to devices has widened, which narrows one divide. But the gap in digital skills and in the quality of access is widening — those with fast internet and tech literacy pull ahead fast. So the surface divide narrows while the meaningful one deepens.', 'Distinguish surface from substance.', ['digital divide', 'literacy', 'surface', 'deepen']],
            ['How might brain-computer interfaces change what it means to be human?', 'If we can think to type or download skills, the boundary between mind and machine blurs profoundly. It could liberate people with disabilities and accelerate learning, but it raises deep questions about identity, privacy and equality. I find it equal parts thrilling and unsettling.', 'Use speculative, philosophical language.', ['brain-computer interface', 'blur', 'identity', 'unsettling']],
            ['Should there be a right to disconnect from technology?', 'I think yes, increasingly so. As work bleeds into personal life through always-on devices, the pressure to be reachable erodes well-being. A legal right to disconnect, as some countries have introduced, would protect people without banning technology. It\'s about restoring choice.', 'Argue for a policy with reasoning.', ['bleed into', 'reachable', 'erode', 'restore']],
        ],
    ],

    // ============================================================
    // 9. HEALTH & WELLNESS
    // ============================================================
    'health-wellness' => [
        'A1' => [
            ['Are you healthy?', 'Yes, I am healthy. I eat fruit and vegetables. I drink water every day. I sleep eight hours.', 'Say yes/no + 2 healthy habits.', ['healthy', 'fruit', 'water', 'sleep']],
            ['Do you exercise?', 'Yes, I exercise. I play football with my friends. I also walk to school.', 'Say yes/no + what you do.', ['exercise', 'football', 'walk', 'school']],
            ['What do you do when you are sick?', 'When I am sick, I stay in bed. I drink warm water. My mother gives me medicine.', 'Describe what you do.', ['sick', 'bed', 'medicine', 'warm water']],
            ['Do you eat fruit?', 'Yes, I eat fruit every day. I like apples and bananas. Fruit is sweet and healthy.', 'Say yes/no + favourite fruit.', ['fruit', 'apple', 'banana', 'sweet']],
            ['How many hours do you sleep?', 'I sleep about eight hours. I go to bed at 10 and wake up at 6. Sleep makes me fresh.', 'Say the number + times.', ['sleep', 'eight hours', 'bed', 'fresh']],
            ['Do you drink water?', 'Yes, I drink a lot of water. I drink six glasses a day. Water is good for my body.', 'Say yes/no + how much.', ['water', 'glass', 'body', 'good']],
        ],
        'A2' => [
            ['How do you stay healthy?', 'I stay healthy by eating good food and exercising. I try to sleep early and drink water. I also avoid too much sugar.', 'List 3–4 healthy habits.', ['stay healthy', 'exercise', 'sugar', 'early']],
            ['What do you do to relax?', 'To relax, I listen to music or take a walk. Sometimes I read a book. A warm shower also helps me relax.', 'List 2–3 relaxation methods.', ['relax', 'music', 'walk', 'shower']],
            ['Do you get enough sleep?', 'Most nights I sleep seven hours, which is okay. But when I have exams, I sleep less and feel tired the next day.', 'Say yes/no + explain.', ['enough sleep', 'seven hours', 'exam', 'tired']],
            ['Talk about a healthy food you like.', 'I like salad with tomatoes and cucumber. It is fresh and light. I eat it for lunch sometimes.', 'Describe the food + why healthy.', ['salad', 'tomato', 'cucumber', 'light']],
            ['What is bad for your health?', 'Smoking and too much fast food are bad for health. Sitting all day is also bad. Not sleeping enough makes me feel awful.', 'List 2–3 unhealthy things.', ['smoking', 'fast food', 'sit', 'awful']],
