        'B2' => [
            ['"Art should comfort the disturbed and disturb the comfortable." Discuss.', 'I think this captures art\'s dual purpose. Great art can soothe suffering by giving it form, and it can unsettle the complacent by exposing what they\'d rather ignore. Art that only comforts or only disturbs is half its potential. The best work does both, often in the same piece.', 'Engage with the duality in the quotation.', ['soothe', 'unsettle', 'complacent', 'potential']],
            ['How does art reflect the society that produces it?', 'Art is both mirror and hammer — it reflects society back to itself and shapes it in turn. The themes artists explore reveal a culture\'s anxieties and hopes, while the work itself shifts public imagination. You can read a society\'s soul in its art across centuries.', 'Use the mirror/hammer metaphor.', ['mirror', 'hammer', 'anxiety', 'imagination']],
            ['Discuss whether art needs to be "useful".', 'I resist the idea that art must justify itself by utility. Some of the most valuable art serves no practical purpose yet transforms how we feel and think. Measuring everything by usefulness shrinks the human experience. Art\'s uselessness is precisely its freedom.', 'Argue against instrumentalisation.', ['utility', 'justify', 'shrink', 'instrumentalisation']],
            ['How has globalisation affected local cultures and arts?', 'Globalisation spreads ideas widely, which can enrich local art with new influences. But it also homogenises, as global media drown out local voices. The cultures that thrive are those that engage with the world without losing themselves — easier said than done.', 'Present the dual effect + the challenge.', ['globalisation', 'homogenise', 'drown out', 'thrive']],
            ['Can AI-generated work be considered art?', 'This is genuinely contested. If art requires human intention and emotion, then AI output is more like a skilled imitation. But if art is judged by its effect on the viewer, some AI work clearly moves people. I think the question itself is evolving faster than our definitions can keep up.', 'Hold a genuinely open, evolving stance.', ['contested', 'intention', 'imitation', 'definition']],
            ['Describe how a piece of art made you see the world differently.', 'Seeing Picasso\'s Guernica in person unsettled me deeply. Its chaos and anguish made war feel visceral in a way no news report ever had. I left understanding that art doesn\'t just depict suffering — it transmits it, which is a form of truth-telling words alone can\'t achieve.', 'Use specific, sensory, reflective language.', ['unsettle', 'visceral', 'anguish', 'transmit']],
